snippet: Dozens of people were killed in the Libyan capital, Tripoli, setting off some of the worst violence there since the revolt against Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi almost three years ago.
abstract: Dozens of people are killed in Tripoli, Libya, when militiamen open fire on unarmed protesters, setting off some of the worst violence in capital since revolt against Col Muammar el-Qaddafi in 2010.
lead_paragraph: Dozens of people were killed in the Libyan capital, Tripoli, setting off some of the worst violence there since the revolt against Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi almost three years ago.
